subject: Make import task capable of running as admin on behalf of user

values.-1: This patch needs further work before it can be merged
values.+1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

Patch Set 1:

Pretend we have a fine-grained method of granting the user to get past my new authorization check. This would pass an admin-enabled ImageRepo to copy-image tasks, and the ImportActionWrapper class would use it to do things like setting the image properties only. Right now, only get_flow() uses this, which is pointless, but it shows that we do that first operation as admin, which is what I was choking on, and what the test I added in HEAD~3 was hitting.

Patch Set 1:

I know this is PoC, Wrapper concept looks fine to me.

Just to note that when I tried this to create image using import in all-stores I saw below behavior.

1. When operation starts os_glance_importing_to_stores doesn't show first store and starts with ',store2,store3,..'
2. When import workflow starts image state never changes to importing
3. After completion of importing image to one store it gets deducted from os_glance_importing_to_stores and appended to os_glance_failed_import (I know this is ToDo, but just wants to highlight)
4. After successful completion of operation, Image remains in uploading state only (I guess that is because we are not passing state to save in wrapper)
